            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>[to U]daydu/ru:<lb/>[PN of the so]ns of Guru jars<lb break="no"/>[j]ars, eleven<lb/>On the
                    4th of Elul, year 4.<lb/>Abdmilk<lb/>(bet)</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p/>
                <p>This chit signifie the payment of 11 jars, and is one in a series of 6 or 7 that
                    are signed by Abdmilk, with a seal of the letter "bet" (ב). It is notable that
                    the number 11 is written out in words as עשר וחדה, instead of merely a numeral.
                    PN=payer name.</p>
            </div>
